                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Roosevelt made no record of the discussion at this meeting. On May 24, 1943,
                    Presidential Assistant Secretary Early announced that Churchill had returned to
                    the White House the previous evening after having spent the weekend as guest of
                    the British Embassy. According to the Early announcement, Roosevelt and
                    Churchill conferred together until 2:30 in the morning. It is likely that at
                    this meeting, Roosevelt and Churchill took up the Memorandum Prepared by the
                    Subcommittee on Territorial Problems, May 22, 1943, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>,
                        <ref target="#pg_338">p. 338</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
